                    </div>
                    <span>This book is definately worth purchasing -- particularly for those new to independent consulting.  Although the copyright date is 1990 (Howard died in the early/mid 1990s and the book hasn't been updated since), most of the material is timeless. It is often difficult for independent consultants to get sample copies of proposals, interim reports, and final reports.  This is particularly the case for those new to consulting without an established peer network.  This book solves that delimma and illustrates the marketing role of the proposal and subsequent interim and final reports.  Are you serious about building your consulting business?  Prove it to yourself: buy a copy of this book today.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A keeper....</div>
